This paper deals with image segmentation using machine learning tools, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of active learning and hierarchical agglomerative segmentation also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the mention of neural tissue and 3D electron microscopy images suggests a possible connection to neuroscience (cs.NE) and medical imaging (cs.MM).
